.TH ZERO_DIVIDE 3S "Sphinx Informix Tools"
.SH NAME
zero_divide \(em do division safely
.SH SYNOPSIS
LET quotient = zero_divide(dividend, divisor)
.SH DESCRIPTION
If both the dividend and the divisor are zero, \fBzero_divide\fP returns zero;
if the divisor is zero, it returns \s-2NULL\s0; otherwise it returns the
quotient (the dividend divided by the divisor).
.P
This is typically used in reports to prevent trouble.
